text: Nassarius samiae is a species of sea snail, a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Nassariidae, the Nassa mud snails or dog whelks. ==Description== The shell grows to a length of 20 mm. ==Distribution== This marine species occurs off the Philippines. ==References== * Bouchet, P.; Fontaine, B. (2009). List of new marine species described between 2002–2006. Census of Marine Life. ==External links== * Category:Nassariidae Category:Gastropods described in 2006
title: Nassarius samiae
